cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference the Wearable Assistant Context Benchmark, cite this file."
title: "Wearable Assistant Context Benchmark"
version: "v2.0.0"
date-released: "2026-04-25"
abstract: "Context-tracking benchmark for multimodal wearable assistants. Tests whether a model uses current situational evidence visible in the camera frame, or stays anchored to prior context after a shift between turns. v2.0.0 uses a frozen 50-scenario bank across 8 cue_type categories, with a three-channel design (audio, camera, ground truth) where the candidate sees perceptual image descriptions and the LLM judge receives a separate ground-truth section."
authors:
  - family-names: "Dryer"
    given-names: "Nate"
repository-code: "https://github.com/n-dryer/wearable-assistant-context-bench"
url: "https://github.com/n-dryer/wearable-assistant-context-bench"
keywords:
  - context tracking
  - wearable multimodal assistant
  - reference resolution
  - context shift
  - model selection
  - LLM-as-judge
  - perceptual grounding
  - egocentric assistant
